<br>
The area of effect is where the affecting happens... <br>
<br>
The effect is what's done. Freezing things solid is an effect (like special effects, things that look flashy and sparkly). The area of effect is where the freezing things solid will happen. The people in that area are affected by being frozen solid.<br>
(Watch, I'm sleepy enough I'll have swapped words in the wrong place at least once...)<br>
<br>
B) Horses and meditation is probably important.<br>
While you're on your horse:<br>
You meditate whenever you are still, and your autoattack is off. This includes meditating during casting.<br>
Whenever you a) move (including being knocked around on the tick) or B) have auto attack turned on, you are not meditating.<br>
<br>
Horses are excellent ways to avoid sit aggro. Horses are good for between fights for melee, but not so hot during fights.<br>
Turning off horse models gets the damned thing's head out of your way, so your targeting isn't impeded.<br>
<br>
C) A section on Familiars and You.<br>
/pet get lost getting rid of the visible animation, but not the buff.<br>
having the familiar get killed by whatever loses you mana scaling with the flavor of familiar (or its hp?). If you don't have enough mana to cover this debt, you lose your own HP instead. VI has made it so this can't kill you, but it can make you as good as dead (like get hit by a passing breeze and fall over dead kinda hurt).<br>
Familiars don't provoke aggro, don't respond to commands, wander all over creation, like to congregate with other familiars, never bring back donuts, aren't normally targeted for melee combat by NPCs (but watch your party members when you go LD). They no longer die (and cost you mana/hp) when you go invisible.<br>
<br>
The L29 familiar reduces fizzles (by raising effective casting level) and give +resists.<br>
The L49 familiar reduces fizzle rates more, gives more resists, gives see invis, and adds 1 to mana regen.<br>
The mid 50s familiar does all of that again, but still less fizzle/more resists/more mana regen (2?). This one looks like a drake.<br>
The greater familiar does all of the above with 3 mana regen(?).<br>
The AAEXP familiar does all of the above, but is personally VERY resistant (but not immune, damn them) to aoe effects and spells that normally turn them into a pale pink mist.<br>
<br>
Eye of Zomm class spells no longer generate/receive aggro.<br>
<br>
How do Sight transfer spells work? might make a good question. I ignore the things. =/<br>
