However....sometimes the mob on you might be an add or a mob that is assisting the tanks mob but leaves the tanks because of an AoE spell (BoF for example).<br>
Some mobs (eg cats in OT) seem to really hate AoE of any kind.<br>
<br>
Because the tanks are busy with a mob they less likely to quickly leave it to save you.<br>
<br>
I found that running to the tanks and then around/though them can cause the mob to leave you for the tanks. It also bring the mob back to the tanks.<br>
<br>
During the time the mob is following you the tanks go up on its aggro list because they are near by hitting one of its buddies.<br>
<br>
On the subject of aggro I also believe that you also gain aggro everytime a mob misses you. This is a part of the process by which a mob that is assisting another mob gains aggro on the attacker.<br>
<br>
I once Evaced myself into sro to see a SG fighting the NPC that doesn't fight back and has very high regen. After medding back most of a mana bar (ie ages). I started nuking the SG,  I had nuked it down to about half health before it left the NPC for me. The was only one other person in sro at the time and if someone had charmed the SG then they where nowhere to be seen and said nothing afterwards. Note the SG's do fight the DE gysies at the tents.<br>
<br>
It is possible that moving vs being still might also be a factor like sitting and standing. If not it should be. While moving you are harder to hit and less of a threat because you can not cast. <br>
<br>
I also believe that debuff aggro is calculated differently. This aggro is higher but decays faster.<br>
I have noticed this with the Staff of Temp flux.<br>
ie being summoned during a raid on Kael. I waited 3 or 4 second while masses of tanks bashed it. Hit the giant once with the SoTF, was summoned but never hit. I was after fraction on very mob.....<br>
<br>
I am thinking that each action has as an initial aggro value,  a decay amount and duration. eg Nuke might be 400 points, -20 points per tick for 20 ticks. A SoTF hit might be 1000 points with -500 points per tick for 2 ticks.<br>
<br>
moozoo lv 52 wizard povar<br>
